Date: 22/11/1957
Source: Letter
Author:
Vol / Page:
Edition:
Quote: ONCER This may be purely local ... A oncer is a man (or purchaser) who is not likely to have occasion to buy the firm's goods more than once a lifetime so can be fobbed off with poor quality stuff. My guess is that it  could also have been used on the West Coast (South Island) ... (timber trade.)
Notes: Muriel Dalton letter (Upper Hutt)

